                <p class="text-small">
                    The crops have to be stored at the recommended level of moisture, which varies for different types
                    of grains. Excess moisture in the crops promotes the growth of micro-organisms and can rot the crops
                    and cause huge losses. Moisture may also germinate the stored seeds, which has to be avoided.
                    <br>Preservation can be defined as, the process of keeping crops safe from spoilage (by
                    maintaining the quality) until they are consumed or sold

